.TH EDIT 1 "2026" "edit v0.9.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
edit \- a terminal text editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B edit
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ file ]
.br
.I command
.B "| edit"
.br
.B "edit \-"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B edit
is a terminal text editor written in C23. It features Unicode/grapheme\-aware
editing, mmap\-based lazy loading for instant file opens, syntax highlighting
for 9 languages, incremental search with regex, mouse support, and multiple
color themes.
.PP
Files of any size open instantly because
.B edit
uses memory\-mapped I/O. Only the visible portion of the file is decoded
into memory.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-tabstop= N
Set the tab display width to
.I N
columns (1\-32). Overrides the config file setting.
.TP
.BI \-\-ruler= N
Display a column ruler at column
.IR N .
Set to 0 to disable.
.TP
.B \-
Read from standard input (pipe mode). After reading, the editor
reopens /dev/tty for interactive editing.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
.SS File Operations
.TP
.BR Alt+S ", " Ctrl+S
Save the current file. Prompts for a filename if unnamed.
.TP
.B Alt+Shift+S
Save as: always prompts for a filename.
.TP
.BR Alt+Q ", " Ctrl+Q
Quit. Prompts to save if there are unsaved changes.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Z
Suspend the editor and return to the shell. Resume with
.BR fg .
.SS Navigation
.TP
.BR "Arrow keys" ", " Alt+HJKL
Move cursor by one character or line.
.TP
.BR Home ", " End ", " Ctrl+A ", " Ctrl+E
Move to beginning or end of line.
.TP
.BR Ctrl+Left ", " Ctrl+Right
Jump by word boundary.
.TP
.BR "Page Up" ", " "Page Down"
Scroll by one screenful.
.TP
.BR Alt+G ", " Ctrl+G
Jump to a specific line number.
.SS Selection
.TP
.B Shift+Arrow
Select by character or line.
.TP
.BR Shift+Ctrl+Left ", " Shift+Ctrl+Right
Select by word.
.TP
.BR Alt+A ", " Alt+E
Select to line start or end.
.TP
.B Mouse drag
Select with the mouse.
.TP
.B ESC
Clear selection.
.SS Clipboard
.TP
.B Alt+C
Copy selection.
.TP
.B Alt+X
Cut selection.
.TP
.B Alt+V
Paste.
.TP
.B Alt+Shift+K
Cut entire line.
.TP
.B Alt+D
Duplicate line.
.SS Editing
.TP
.B Enter
Insert newline with auto\-indent.
.TP
.BR Ctrl+U
Undo.
.TP
.BR Ctrl+R
Redo.
.TP
.B Tab
Insert tab, or indent selection.
.TP
.B Shift+Tab
Dedent selection.
.TP
.B Alt+/
Toggle line comment (filetype\-aware).
.TP
.B Alt+]
Jump to matching bracket.
.SS Search
.TP
.BR Alt+F ", " Ctrl+F
Incremental search. Left/Right navigate matches, Up/Down browse
search history. Enter accepts, ESC cancels.
.TP
.B Alt+C
Toggle case sensitivity during search.
.TP
.B Alt+X
Toggle regex mode during search (POSIX ERE).
.TP
.B Alt+R
Find and replace.
.SS Display
.TP
.B Alt+T
Cycle color theme (persisted to config).
.TP
.B Alt+N
Toggle line numbers.
.TP
.B Alt+W
Toggle soft word wrap.
.TP
.BR F11 ", " Alt+?
Show help screen.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B edit
reads configuration from
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/edit/config
(defaults to
.IR ~/.config/edit/config ).
.PP
The config file uses a simple key = value format.
Lines starting with # are comments.
.PP
.RS
.nf
# Example configuration
tabstop = 4
theme = Cyberpunk
line_numbers = true
ruler = 80
.fi
.RE
.SS Configuration Keys
.TP
.B tabstop
Tab display width in columns (1\-32). Default: 8.
.TP
.B theme
Color theme name. Default: Cyberpunk. Available: Cyberpunk, Nightwatch,
Daywatch, Tokyo Night, Akira, Tokyo Cyberpunk, Clarity.
.TP
.B line_numbers
Show line number gutter (true/false). Default: true.
.TP
.B ruler
Column ruler position (0 to disable). Default: 0.
.SH THEMES
All themes use 24\-bit RGB color. Cycle at runtime with Alt+T.
.TP
.B Cyberpunk
Dark background with neon magenta, cyan, and green accents.
.TP
.B Nightwatch
Monochrome dark palette using shades of gray.
.TP
.B Daywatch
Monochrome light palette with dark text on near\-white.
.TP
.B "Tokyo Night"
Deep indigo base with soft purple, blue, and green.
.TP
.B Akira
Neo\-Tokyo red and cyan on a warm dark base.
.TP
.B "Tokyo Cyberpunk"
Tokyo Night's indigo base with neon accents.
.TP
.B Clarity
Colorblind\-accessible blue/orange/yellow palette.
.SH SYNTAX HIGHLIGHTING
Syntax highlighting activates automatically based on file extension.
Supported languages: C/C++ (.c, .h, .cpp), Python (.py), JavaScript
(.js, .jsx, .mjs), Go (.go), Rust (.rs), Bash (.sh, .bash), JSON
(.json), YAML (.yml, .yaml), Markdown (.md, .markdown).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B COLORTERM
If set to "truecolor" or "24bit", confirms true color support.
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for the configuration file. Defaults to ~/.config.
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Base directory for cursor position history. Defaults to ~/.local/share.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/edit/config
Configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/edit/cursor_history
Remembered cursor positions per file.
.TP
.I <file>.edit.swp
Swap file for crash recovery, created alongside the edited file.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Normal exit.
.TP
.B 1
Fatal error (terminal I/O failure, out of memory).
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at https://github.com/deths74r/edit/issues
